WEBVTT

1
00:01:21.126 --> 00:01:23.286
It's taking so long.

2
00:01:24.326 --> 00:01:27.846
Look at yourself. Father.

3
00:01:27.926 --> 00:01:30.206
You'd think
this was your first child.

4
00:01:30.286 --> 00:01:33.766
Tell me. were you this nervous
when I was born?

5
00:01:33.846 --> 00:01:37.326
Well. yes and no.
It was different with your mother.

6
00:01:37.406 --> 00:01:39.566
But with Rachel. we gave up hope.

7
00:01:39.646 --> 00:01:42.486
We were told
she could never have children.

8
00:01:42.566 --> 00:01:45.606
- Father! It's a boy!
- Father.

9
00:01:45.686 --> 00:01:47.846
- Father. it's a boy!
- It's a boy.

10
00:01:50.006 --> 00:01:51.086
My boy!

11
00:01:54.366 --> 00:01:58.006
Can you believe it?
Rachel had a baby.

12
00:01:58.086 --> 00:02:00.446
I guess it is a miracle.

13
00:02:09.486 --> 00:02:12.166
O God. who is the father of us all.

14
00:02:12.246 --> 00:02:16.806
you have blessed me
with a gift beyond all measure.

15
00:02:16.886 --> 00:02:19.046
Within a barren wife.

16
00:02:19.126 --> 00:02:22.086
amid the twilight skies of my life.

17
00:02:22.166 --> 00:02:24.406
you've placed a treasure.

18
00:02:24.486 --> 00:02:28.966
<i># A brightly shining star
where there was none</i>

19
00:02:29.046 --> 00:02:32.486
<i># You have granted us a son</i>

20
00:02:32.566 --> 00:02:34.366
<i># Dreams do come true.</i>

21
00:02:34.446 --> 00:02:36.286
<i>- # Look at you
- # Joseph</i>

22
00:02:36.406 --> 00:02:38.926
<i># Our baby brother
# He is special</i>

23
00:02:39.006 --> 00:02:42.406
<i># He is one of us.
we'll keep him from harm</i>

24
00:02:42.486 --> 00:02:44.886
<i># And we will teach him</i>

25
00:02:44.966 --> 00:02:47.566
<i># I will teach him
all he needs to know</i>

26
00:02:47.646 --> 00:02:50.286
<i># He'll stand apart from other men</i>

27
00:02:50.366 --> 00:02:52.606
<i># We'll stand beside him and together</i>

28
00:02:52.686 --> 00:02:58.366
<i># We will show him
what it means to be a family... #</i>

29
00:02:59.806 --> 00:03:01.806
Ah. Ooh.

30
00:03:01.886 --> 00:03:06.406
<i># You are a miracle child</i>

31
00:03:06.486 --> 00:03:07.926
<i># You are the best</i>

32
00:03:08.006 --> 00:03:10.486
<i># You shine the brightest... #</i>

33
00:03:10.566 --> 00:03:14.246
Joseph.

34
00:03:14.326 --> 00:03:17.366
Come on. Come to Papa.

35
00:03:17.446 --> 00:03:19.446
<i># Your trails be blessed</i>

36
00:03:19.526 --> 00:03:21.286
<i># Your trials the lightest</i>

37
00:03:21.366 --> 00:03:23.366
<i># You were made for better things</i>

38
00:03:23.446 --> 00:03:25.846
<i># You will share the air of kings</i>

39
00:03:25.926 --> 00:03:30.326
<i># You were born and fortune smiled</i>

40
00:03:30.406 --> 00:03:34.726
<i># For you are a miracle child</i>

41
00:03:37.606 --> 00:03:39.446
<i># The sun will rise</i>

42
00:03:39.526 --> 00:03:41.606
<i># Within your eyes</i>

43
00:03:41.686 --> 00:03:46.366
<i># The moon will light your smile</i>

44
00:03:46.446 --> 00:03:50.686
<i># And Heaven grace your gentle face</i>

45
00:03:50.766 --> 00:03:54.486
<i>- # With power to beguile... #
- Good night. Joseph.</i>

46
00:03:54.566 --> 00:03:58.406
<i># You will wade through
the river of sorrows</i>

47
00:03:58.526 --> 00:04:01.486
<i># Warm and dry</i>

48
00:04:01.566 --> 00:04:05.246
<i># And angels
will guide your tomorrows</i>

49
00:04:05.326 --> 00:04:08.486
<i># This I prophesy</i>

50
00:04:08.566 --> 00:04:13.006
<i># For you are a miracle child</i>

51
00:04:13.086 --> 00:04:15.766
<i># You are the best</i>

52
00:04:15.846 --> 00:04:18.286
<i># You shine the brightest</i>

53
00:04:18.366 --> 00:04:23.366
<i># Your days will be cloudless
and mild</i>

54
00:04:23.486 --> 00:04:25.686
<i># Your trails be blessed</i>

55
00:04:25.766 --> 00:04:27.806
<i># Your trials the lightest</i>

56
00:04:27.886 --> 00:04:30.766
<i># You were made for better things</i>

57
00:04:30.846 --> 00:04:33.206
<i># You will share the air of kings</i>

58
00:04:33.286 --> 00:04:36.886
<i># You were born and fortune smiled</i>

59
00:04:36.966 --> 00:04:42.926
<i># For you are a miracle child</i>

60
00:04:55.686 --> 00:04:58.046
<i># Dearest Mother</i>

61
00:04:58.126 --> 00:05:00.166
<i># Beloved Father</i>

62
00:05:00.246 --> 00:05:04.726
<i># A coat of colours
bright as butterfly wings</i>

63
00:05:04.806 --> 00:05:06.726
<i># To remind me</i>

64
00:05:06.806 --> 00:05:08.966
<i># Things you've told me all my life</i>

65
00:05:09.046 --> 00:05:10.966
<i># I am special. I am smart</i>

66
00:05:11.046 --> 00:05:13.446
<i># I am somehow set apart</i>

67
00:05:13.526 --> 00:05:17.126
<i># Petty rules and limitations
don't apply</i>

68
00:05:17.206 --> 00:05:19.766
<i># For I</i>

69
00:05:19.846 --> 00:05:22.646
<i># Am a miracle child</i>

70
00:05:22.726 --> 00:05:24.526
<i># I can't be harmed</i>

71
00:05:24.646 --> 00:05:27.446
<i># I'm wrapped in rainbows</i>

72
00:05:27.526 --> 00:05:32.686
<i># Though fate
can be heartless and vile</i>

73
00:05:32.766 --> 00:05:35.166
<i># My life's been charmed</i>

74
00:05:35.246 --> 00:05:36.926
<i># And shall remain so</i>

75
00:05:37.006 --> 00:05:39.726
<i># I was made for something more</i>

76
00:05:39.806 --> 00:05:42.606
<i># Not to struggle but to soar</i>

77
00:05:42.686 --> 00:05:47.006
<i># To my fortune reconciled</i>

78
00:05:47.086 --> 00:05:52.966
<i># For I am a miracle child</i>

79
00:05:53.046 --> 00:05:56.166
<i># You won't see me bent over double</i>

80
00:05:56.246 --> 00:05:58.126
<i># In darkness and rubble</i>

81
00:05:58.206 --> 00:06:01.606
<i># Where mountains of trouble
are piled</i>

82
00:06:01.686 --> 00:06:03.606
<i># I was destined to fly</i>

83
00:06:03.686 --> 00:06:08.246
<i># Watch me light up the sky</i>

84
00:06:08.326 --> 00:06:13.286
<i># For I am a miracle child #</i>

85
00:07:23.446 --> 00:07:26.606
Hey...

86
00:07:26.686 --> 00:07:29.086
- No! Stop!
- What's wrong?

87
00:07:29.166 --> 00:07:31.366
- What's going on?
- What did he say?

88
00:07:31.486 --> 00:07:33.846
- Oh. it's Joseph.
- It was wolves!

89
00:07:33.926 --> 00:07:36.846
Coming out of the shadows.
I was surrounded.

90
00:07:36.926 --> 00:07:39.366
- They were all around...
- That's it?

91
00:07:39.446 --> 00:07:42.366
- You woke us...for a dream?
- Ooh!

92
00:07:42.446 --> 00:07:45.046
Quiet! You want to scare the sheep?

93
00:07:45.126 --> 00:07:47.926
The sheep. The ram.

94
00:07:48.006 --> 00:07:50.846
The wolves killed the ram.

95
00:07:50.926 --> 00:07:55.846
It was dead. I... I don't understand.
It all seemed so real.

96
00:07:55.926 --> 00:08:01.006
- Everything is fine. Joseph.
- It's over. Don't worry.

97
00:08:01.086 --> 00:08:04.406
Boys. since you're up.
make yourselves useful.

98
00:08:04.486 --> 00:08:06.406
Get to work before sunup.

99
00:08:08.806 --> 00:08:10.726
Thanks

100
00:08:15.126 --> 00:08:17.726
- Joseph. where are you going?
- Um. I...

101
00:08:17.806 --> 00:08:20.286
You have studies.

102
00:08:20.366 --> 00:08:22.766
But. I wanna go with them.

103
00:08:22.846 --> 00:08:26.806
- They have their work and you yours.
- But why?

104
00:08:26.886 --> 00:08:30.086
Because you do.
Because you're a miracle child.

105
00:08:30.166 --> 00:08:32.566
For you things are different.

106
00:08:32.686 --> 00:08:36.126
I don't want to be different.
I want to be like them.

107
00:08:36.206 --> 00:08:40.006
Joseph. God has a plan
and a purpose for you.

108
00:08:40.086 --> 00:08:42.686
You're not like the rest of us.

109
00:08:42.766 --> 00:08:47.406
I've worked this earth all my life.
just as my father and grandfather did

110
00:08:47.486 --> 00:08:49.646
and your brothers will after me.

111
00:08:49.726 --> 00:08:51.646
That won't be your future.

112
00:08:51.726 --> 00:08:54.486
Jacob. even God
rested on the seventh day.

113
00:08:54.566 --> 00:08:56.886
He'll find his future soon enough.

114
00:08:56.966 --> 00:08:59.926
- Let him be with his brothers.
- Please?

115
00:09:01.246 --> 00:09:03.326
Go on.

116
00:09:04.446 --> 00:09:06.526
Thanks.

117
00:09:06.606 --> 00:09:08.766
Be safe!

118
00:09:16.166 --> 00:09:17.726
Judah! Simeon!

119
00:09:19.166 --> 00:09:21.966
- Hmph! Look who's here.
- The miracle child.

120
00:09:22.046 --> 00:09:25.686
What are you doing?
Don't you have some scrolls to read?

121
00:09:25.766 --> 00:09:27.606
Here. let me do that.

122
00:09:27.686 --> 00:09:30.886
Wait. wait!
You have to be very careful.

123
00:09:30.966 --> 00:09:33.686
- You'll cut your hands on the fur
- Get away!

124
00:09:33.766 --> 00:09:37.166
I... I just want to help.

125
00:09:37.246 --> 00:09:40.686
Thanks to you. we'll have to
work an extra hour today.

126
00:09:40.766 --> 00:09:43.806
You're tired
because you were out all night.

127
00:09:43.886 --> 00:09:47.166
Why. you little sneak...
What do you know?

128
00:09:47.246 --> 00:09:50.166
Everything.
The women and the drinking...

129
00:09:50.246 --> 00:09:53.326
- There's a lot Father doesn't know.
- You wouldn't?

130
00:09:53.406 --> 00:09:55.206
He would. the brat.

131
00:09:55.326 --> 00:09:58.486
- One word and I'll wring your neck.
- Stop it!

132
00:09:58.566 --> 00:10:00.926
We should be happy for his help.

133
00:10:01.006 --> 00:10:04.486
Maybe he can do your work. Simeon.
Somebody should.

134
00:10:06.086 --> 00:10:08.606
And there is something Joseph can do.

135
00:10:08.686 --> 00:10:11.566
- What's he doing?
- Shh!

136
00:10:11.646 --> 00:10:15.166
While we round up the strays.
can you watch the herd?

137
00:10:15.246 --> 00:10:17.406
- Of course.
- Good.

138
00:10:17.486 --> 00:10:20.126
We'll be back soon. Let's go.

139
00:10:20.206 --> 00:10:23.166
Maybe we should split up.
You go over there.

140
00:10:23.246 --> 00:10:26.766
- I'll go this way.
- Hey! What are you doing?

141
00:10:43.726 --> 00:10:46.566
Whoo-hoo!

142
00:10:46.646 --> 00:10:48.886
- Get him.
- You're too heavy.

143
00:11:00.086 --> 00:11:01.886
What?

144
00:11:01.966 --> 00:11:04.806
Are you making fun of me too?

145
00:11:09.886 --> 00:11:14.126
Hey! Hey. come back!

146
00:11:17.646 --> 00:11:19.686
Huh?

147
00:11:25.166 --> 00:11:26.926
Get away! Get away!

148
00:11:34.566 --> 00:11:37.086
Gotcha!

149
00:11:48.166 --> 00:11:50.246
Back! Back!

150
00:11:50.326 --> 00:11:53.366
Get away!

151
00:11:59.446 --> 00:12:02.486
Joseph. are you hurt?

152
00:12:02.606 --> 00:12:05.086
Father!

153
00:12:05.166 --> 00:12:07.966
Your brothers. where are they?

154
00:12:08.046 --> 00:12:10.966
I asked you a question!

155
00:12:11.046 --> 00:12:13.846
They're...they're. uh...

156
00:12:13.926 --> 00:12:16.446
They...they went swimming.

157
00:12:16.566 --> 00:12:19.166
Swimming?

158
00:12:19.246 --> 00:12:22.486
- What happened?
- This is how you take charge?

159
00:12:22.566 --> 00:12:25.846
I expect you to watch out for Joseph.
but you abandoned my son!

160
00:12:25.926 --> 00:12:28.566
- My son!
- Aren't we your sons too?

161
00:12:28.646 --> 00:12:31.046
The ram!

162
00:12:32.726 --> 00:12:35.926
It's Joseph's dream!

163
00:12:36.006 --> 00:12:39.526
Wolves kill sheep.
It happens all the time.

164
00:12:39.646 --> 00:12:42.686
No! I understand.

165
00:12:44.326 --> 00:12:47.206
God sent you a vision of the future.

166
00:12:48.526 --> 00:12:52.886
Joseph didn't really
see the future. did he?

167
00:12:55.086 --> 00:12:57.046
Let's get back to work.

168
00:13:42.206 --> 00:13:44.206
Why do we wash before work?

169
00:13:44.286 --> 00:13:46.566
We don't want the sheep smelling you!

170
00:13:46.646 --> 00:13:49.366
Look who finally woke up.

171
00:13:49.446 --> 00:13:52.966
- Look what the sun brought up.
- Nice of you to join us.

172
00:13:53.046 --> 00:13:55.046
Good morning. Joseph.

173
00:13:55.126 --> 00:13:57.486
Mom. last night I had another dream.

174
00:13:57.566 --> 00:13:59.526
- Oh. another dream!
- Ooh!

175
00:13:59.606 --> 00:14:03.366
- I wasn't talking to you.
- Please. why don't you share it?

176
00:14:03.446 --> 00:14:05.286
Who'd the wolf get this time?

177
00:14:05.366 --> 00:14:07.846
You can laugh. but it was about you.

178
00:14:07.926 --> 00:14:12.646
Oh. please. you must tell us
our future. great Joseph!

179
00:14:12.726 --> 00:14:15.406
- Leave me alone!
- Come on. tell us.

180
00:14:15.486 --> 00:14:18.126
We're dying to hear about it.

181
00:14:18.206 --> 00:14:20.566
We were carrying sheaves of wheat.

182
00:14:20.646 --> 00:14:22.206
I was among you.

183
00:14:22.286 --> 00:14:26.806
but then all of a sudden I was above
you and your wheat bowed to me...

184
00:14:26.926 --> 00:14:30.446
- I wonder what that means.
- Nothing. that's what.

185
00:14:30.526 --> 00:14:32.846
Hey. you asked to hear the dream.

186
00:14:32.926 --> 00:14:34.486
What happened next?

187
00:14:34.566 --> 00:14:37.286
The sky was dark
and all around me were stars

188
00:14:37.366 --> 00:14:42.006
- They were bowing to me too.
- Ooh! Let's all bow down to Joseph!

189
00:14:42.086 --> 00:14:46.086
We can't ignore these dreams.
After all. his last one came true.

190
00:14:46.166 --> 00:14:50.726
Are you saying that Joseph belongs
above all of us. even Judah?

191
00:14:50.806 --> 00:14:54.806
I'm not saying that.
but there could be a message here.

192
00:14:54.886 --> 00:14:58.606
Judah's led the herd for years.
brought in the wheat...

193
00:14:58.726 --> 00:15:02.246
He comes first before any of us -
especially Joseph.

194
00:15:02.326 --> 00:15:04.726
Judah. it's not up to me.

195
00:15:04.806 --> 00:15:07.806
God may be telling us
something of our future.

196
00:15:07.886 --> 00:15:11.246
- Then my work doesn't matter.
- Watch your tongue.

197
00:15:11.326 --> 00:15:13.446
Jacob. Judah. please!

198
00:15:13.526 --> 00:15:17.286
- I've had enough of this.
- Let's go.

199
00:15:17.366 --> 00:15:20.406
Look at
what your dreams have done.

200
00:15:20.486 --> 00:15:23.126
Don't get mad at me.
I didn't ask for them.

201
00:15:23.206 --> 00:15:26.886
- Or this either. brother!
- Half-brother!

202
00:15:26.966 --> 00:15:30.806
Joseph! Boys!
Apologise to each other!

203
00:15:30.886 --> 00:15:32.846
Let me talk to Joseph.

204
00:15:38.566 --> 00:15:41.366
He's just a boy.
You're too harsh on him.

205
00:15:41.446 --> 00:15:43.406
You're always defending him!

206
00:15:44.326 --> 00:15:46.886
His dreams come from God.

207
00:15:46.966 --> 00:15:51.846
Joseph. you need to be
more understanding of your brothers.

208
00:15:51.926 --> 00:15:54.966
Life is harder for them
than it will be for you.

209
00:15:55.046 --> 00:15:58.726
Why do you defend them?
They're not even your sons.

210
00:15:58.806 --> 00:16:02.006
They're no less my sons than you are.

211
00:16:02.086 --> 00:16:04.886
We're family. all of us.

212
00:16:06.566 --> 00:16:09.646
If we break apart.
we have nothing left.

213
00:16:12.486 --> 00:16:16.526
<i># You've seen the damage words can do</i>

214
00:16:16.606 --> 00:16:20.606
<i># When full of thoughtless pride</i>

215
00:16:21.646 --> 00:16:26.206
<i># Now heed the wiser voice in you</i>

216
00:16:26.286 --> 00:16:30.966
<i># That calls to be your guide</i>

217
00:16:32.246 --> 00:16:36.286
<i># The flowers reaching for the sun</i>

218
00:16:36.366 --> 00:16:39.846
<i># Are all uniquely blessed</i>

219
00:16:39.926 --> 00:16:43.766
<i># But though each is special</i>

220
00:16:43.846 --> 00:16:47.646
<i># Not a one is better</i>

221
00:16:47.726 --> 00:16:50.326
<i># Than the rest</i>

222
00:16:51.326 --> 00:16:55.326
<i># Bloom. bloom. may you know</i>

223
00:16:55.406 --> 00:16:59.886
<i># The wisdom only time breeds</i>

224
00:16:59.966 --> 00:17:04.806
<i># There's room. bloom and you'll grow</i>

225
00:17:04.886 --> 00:17:09.926
<i># To follow where your heart leads</i>

226
00:17:10.006 --> 00:17:13.926
<i># Bloom and may you bring</i>

227
00:17:14.006 --> 00:17:18.886
<i># Your colours to the vast bouquet</i>

228
00:17:18.966 --> 00:17:23.046
<i># There's room. bloom.
learn one thing</i>

229
00:17:23.126 --> 00:17:29.766
<i># Your gifts are meant to give away #</i>

230
00:17:31.326 --> 00:17:33.286
Thanks. Mom.

231
00:17:48.006 --> 00:17:49.926
Judah! Simeon!

232
00:17:50.006 --> 00:17:51.806
Levi! Reuben!

233
00:17:51.886 --> 00:17:53.766
Where are you?

234
00:17:53.846 --> 00:17:58.486
- Joseph couldn't lead sheep.
- But he's our brother.

235
00:17:58.566 --> 00:18:01.806
Half brother.
Judah should take over.

236
00:18:01.886 --> 00:18:04.486
- But...
- Do you want Joseph in charge?

237
00:18:04.566 --> 00:18:07.926
We agree that something
has to be done about Joseph?

238
00:18:08.006 --> 00:18:10.366
- Absolutely.
- Yes.

239
00:18:10.446 --> 00:18:13.286
- Hey! The spy is back!
- I wasn't spying!

240
00:18:13.366 --> 00:18:16.126
- Did Father tell you to check on us?
- No!

241
00:18:16.246 --> 00:18:18.806
- I want to...
- Report on us to Father?

242
00:18:18.886 --> 00:18:20.966
- You're his favourite.
- N-no.

243
00:18:21.046 --> 00:18:23.846
You look at scrolls all day
while we sweat.

244
00:18:23.926 --> 00:18:27.646
Why is that? Is it because
we don't have pretty coats?

245
00:18:27.726 --> 00:18:30.486
- I have mine.
- That's my coat!

246
00:18:30.566 --> 00:18:33.806
Step aside.
I'm the new head of the family.

247
00:18:33.886 --> 00:18:36.446
Bow before me.
you sheaves of wheat!

248
00:18:36.526 --> 00:18:39.326
Oh. yes. Master Joseph.
ruler of the world.

249
00:18:39.406 --> 00:18:41.006
Give it back. now!

250
00:18:41.086 --> 00:18:44.766
If you want your coat.
why don't you go get it?

251
00:18:44.846 --> 00:18:48.006
- Levi's got it.
- No. I don't. Judah does.

252
00:18:48.086 --> 00:18:49.926
- Come on!
- I've got it!

253
00:18:56.086 --> 00:18:58.966
- I've had enough of this game!
- Joseph!

254
00:18:59.046 --> 00:19:00.966
Who says this is a game?

255
00:19:03.126 --> 00:19:07.046
What are you doing? Leave me alone!
No! Stop it!

256
00:19:10.086 --> 00:19:12.246
Oh! Ohh!

257
00:19:19.286 --> 00:19:21.646
What do we do now?

258
00:19:21.726 --> 00:19:25.086
Are we just going to leave him there?

259
00:19:25.166 --> 00:19:28.246
- We'll think of something.
- Somebody!

260
00:19:28.326 --> 00:19:32.726
- Just get out of here.
- Maybe he can dream his way out.

261
00:19:35.046 --> 00:19:37.046
Don't leave me here alone!

262
00:19:57.766 --> 00:19:59.446
Aah! Aah!

263
00:20:13.366 --> 00:20:15.286
I knew you'd come back.

264
00:20:20.446 --> 00:20:24.846
You think this is funny?
Father won't be laughing when...

265
00:20:24.926 --> 00:20:26.846
- Who are you?
- Get him.

266
00:20:26.926 --> 00:20:29.326
Hey! Hey! What are you doing? Ow!

267
00:20:29.406 --> 00:20:33.406
Let me go! You don't understand.
I'm from the house of Jacob!

268
00:20:33.486 --> 00:20:36.446
- Scrawny. isn't he?
- It's hard to tell.

269
00:20:38.526 --> 00:20:41.406
- Hmm.
- No. no. no. don't take my...

270
00:20:41.486 --> 00:20:44.326
Get up!

271
00:20:44.406 --> 00:20:47.966
Looks like he's never worked a day.

272
00:20:48.046 --> 00:20:50.286
That'll change.

273
00:20:50.366 --> 00:20:53.206
My brothers will come for me. Judah!

274
00:20:53.326 --> 00:20:56.486
- Simeon! Levi! Please help me!
- Joseph!

275
00:20:56.566 --> 00:20:59.126
We're right here.

276
00:20:59.206 --> 00:21:01.326
Judah.

277
00:21:05.606 --> 00:21:07.966
I told you they'd come for me.

278
00:21:10.006 --> 00:21:13.526
As agreed. 20 pieces of silver.

279
00:21:18.246 --> 00:21:20.526
J-Judah... Why...?

280
00:21:24.406 --> 00:21:27.206
No! Help me!

281
00:21:27.286 --> 00:21:30.086
Levi. please. Issachar.

282
00:21:30.166 --> 00:21:32.086
Simeon. Stop them.

283
00:21:32.166 --> 00:21:34.926
Judah. Judah. help me. please.

284
00:21:35.006 --> 00:21:36.886
Please!

285
00:21:43.726 --> 00:21:46.326
Judah. please!

286
00:21:47.406 --> 00:21:51.526
Judah. we can't turn back now.
We've gone too far.

287
00:21:51.606 --> 00:21:53.766
- Aah!
- Hut. hut!

288
00:21:56.806 --> 00:21:59.246
I'm your brother!

289
00:21:59.526 --> 00:22:02.686
I'm your brother!

290
00:22:02.766 --> 00:22:05.366
Half-brother.

291
00:22:05.446 --> 00:22:08.006
Yah!

292
00:22:44.326 --> 00:22:47.286
- Where could he have gone?
- Don't worry.

293
00:22:47.366 --> 00:22:50.046
I'm sure he's all right.

294
00:22:50.126 --> 00:22:52.406
The boys will find him.

295
00:22:52.526 --> 00:22:54.726
Father.

296
00:22:55.806 --> 00:22:58.406
This is all we found.

297
00:22:59.726 --> 00:23:01.726
Joseph!

298
00:23:01.806 --> 00:23:04.246
- No! Joseph!
- Joseph!

299
00:23:07.046 --> 00:23:09.446
Oh. Rachel.

300
00:23:11.446 --> 00:23:13.886
Hey. wake up.

301
00:23:50.286 --> 00:23:54.246
<i># Behold the glory
behold the wonder</i>

302
00:23:54.326 --> 00:23:56.846
<i># What we have made
shall not be torn asunder</i>

303
00:23:56.926 --> 00:23:59.686
<i># Such vast achievement
stone and papyrus</i>

304
00:23:59.766 --> 00:24:02.486
<i># Beneath the gaze
of Isis and Osiris</i>

305
00:24:02.566 --> 00:24:05.686
<i># Land of majesty</i>

306
00:24:05.766 --> 00:24:09.606
<i># Where the heavens smile</i>

307
00:24:09.686 --> 00:24:13.046
<i># Jewel of history shining</i>

308
00:24:13.126 --> 00:24:16.366
<i># By the Nile #</i>

309
00:24:20.846 --> 00:24:23.206
- Exquisite. aren't they?
- Yes.

310
00:24:23.286 --> 00:24:26.086
- Where's the slave market?
- By the docks.

311
00:24:30.206 --> 00:24:31.886
<i># Serve and be silent</i>

312
00:24:31.966 --> 00:24:33.526
<i># You who are chattel</i>

313
00:24:33.606 --> 00:24:36.526
<i># We think of you
as little more than cattle</i>

314
00:24:36.606 --> 00:24:39.526
<i># This is your lot now
and we advise you</i>

315
00:24:39.606 --> 00:24:42.766
<i># To bow before
whatever master buys you</i>

316
00:24:42.846 --> 00:24:46.126
<i># Feel the power here</i>

317
00:24:46.206 --> 00:24:48.886
<i># Power has its price</i>

318
00:24:48.966 --> 00:24:52.046
<i># Some can live like gods</i>

319
00:24:52.126 --> 00:24:54.806
<i># Some must sacrifice... #</i>

320
00:24:54.886 --> 00:24:57.766
- What do you have?
- A Canaanite.

321
00:24:57.846 --> 00:25:01.406
<i># Through the centuries
many backs have bent</i>

322
00:25:01.486 --> 00:25:03.326
<i># Many dreams are built</i>

323
00:25:03.406 --> 00:25:07.366
<i>- # Many lives are spent #
- Move. slave!</i>

324
00:25:07.486 --> 00:25:09.246
Get in line.

325
00:25:09.326 --> 00:25:12.606
Slaves for sale!
Buy this one!

326
00:25:12.686 --> 00:25:15.926
Let's have a look.
Let me see his teeth.

327
00:25:16.006 --> 00:25:18.886
Hmm. Mm-hmm.

328
00:25:18.966 --> 00:25:21.646
He's too skinny.

329
00:25:21.726 --> 00:25:23.326
This is more like it.

330
00:25:23.406 --> 00:25:27.166
The captain of the guard
needs a slave for his household.

331
00:25:27.246 --> 00:25:28.806
I have one he might like.

332
00:25:30.326 --> 00:25:32.286
Thirty pieces? Hmm.

333
00:25:32.366 --> 00:25:35.406
He looks healthy enough.
Lord Potiphar!

334
00:25:37.086 --> 00:25:41.086
- He'll do.
- Looks like we have some work to do.

335
00:25:41.166 --> 00:25:45.326
<i># Look and be humbled
learn what your place is</i>

336
00:25:45.406 --> 00:25:48.286
<i># Egyptian slave
no matter what your race is</i>

337
00:25:48.366 --> 00:25:51.246
<i># This is your future
your life suspended</i>

338
00:25:51.326 --> 00:25:54.286
<i># And everything
you knew before has ended</i>

339
00:25:54.446 --> 00:25:57.446
<i># You are Egypt's now</i>

340
00:25:57.526 --> 00:26:00.806
<i># We have all control</i>

341
00:26:00.886 --> 00:26:02.886
<i># From your every step</i>

342
00:26:02.966 --> 00:26:06.966
<i># To your very soul #
- Hold still.</i>

343
00:26:07.046 --> 00:26:09.606
You're done. He's ready for work.

344
00:26:20.926 --> 00:26:24.126
It's not for your face.
It's for the floor.

345
00:26:31.446 --> 00:26:33.606
Ow!

346
00:26:36.806 --> 00:26:39.766
'Hey. Joseph. you missed a spot.'

347
00:26:39.846 --> 00:26:42.246
'Real work's different.'

348
00:26:42.326 --> 00:26:46.326
- 'No more baby soft hands.'
- 'Who bows now. little brother? '

349
00:26:52.926 --> 00:26:55.046
You there.

350
00:26:56.126 --> 00:26:59.526
Have you cleaned
this entire courtyard yourself?

351
00:26:59.606 --> 00:27:02.326
- Yes.
- He's a hard worker.

352
00:27:02.406 --> 00:27:04.806
Hmm.

353
00:27:04.886 --> 00:27:07.486
We could put him
to better use inside?

354
00:27:07.566 --> 00:27:11.206
My wife thinks you should work
for her. What do you say?

355
00:27:11.286 --> 00:27:13.486
I cannot say.

356
00:27:13.566 --> 00:27:15.606
A slave is not his own master.

357
00:27:16.806 --> 00:27:18.566
Well said.

358
00:27:18.646 --> 00:27:22.606
Find him some new clothes.
Then get someone else to finish.

359
00:27:34.566 --> 00:27:38.326
Here. kitty. kitty. kitty! Come on.

360
00:27:38.406 --> 00:27:41.766
Who brought the cat?

361
00:27:41.846 --> 00:27:44.486
- Here. kitty. kitty. kitty.
- Stop!

362
00:27:44.566 --> 00:27:46.726
Come down!

363
00:27:46.806 --> 00:27:49.766
Aunt Zuleika. I'm sorry.
I'll get it down.

364
00:27:49.846 --> 00:27:52.126
Please come down.

365
00:27:54.246 --> 00:27:57.286
Come here. Look at this.

366
00:27:57.366 --> 00:27:59.446
Oh.

367
00:27:59.526 --> 00:28:02.726
Hmm. She seems to like you.

368
00:28:02.806 --> 00:28:05.886
Thank you.

369
00:28:05.966 --> 00:28:08.766
I haven't seen you here before.

370
00:28:08.846 --> 00:28:10.846
- Oh. I'm new.
- Asenath.

371
00:28:10.926 --> 00:28:14.686
Coming. Aunt Zuleika. Goodbye.

372
00:28:22.206 --> 00:28:24.286
Joseph. come here.

373
00:28:24.366 --> 00:28:26.366
I'm waiting.

374
00:28:26.446 --> 00:28:28.406
I'm coming!

375
00:28:30.646 --> 00:28:32.566
Oh! Sorry. Asenath.

376
00:28:32.646 --> 00:28:34.366
- Oh!
- What?

377
00:28:34.446 --> 00:28:37.726
You don't want my aunt
seeing you like this.

378
00:28:37.846 --> 00:28:39.806
- That's better.
- Thanks.

379
00:28:39.886 --> 00:28:41.926
Slave.

380
00:28:42.006 --> 00:28:45.246
Oh. yes. of course.

381
00:28:49.046 --> 00:28:52.726
Hyah! Hyah!

382
00:28:52.806 --> 00:28:55.686
What a magnificent animal.

383
00:28:58.806 --> 00:29:01.966
Slave. I'm in the sun.

384
00:29:06.246 --> 00:29:08.286
Whoa!

385
00:29:08.406 --> 00:29:10.246
- Well?
- You were right.

386
00:29:10.326 --> 00:29:12.126
He's all that you promised.

387
00:29:12.206 --> 00:29:15.166
I haven't seen a finer horse
in all of Egypt.

388
00:29:15.246 --> 00:29:17.886
I'm glad Your Excellency is pleased.

389
00:29:17.966 --> 00:29:22.246
- There is still one small matter.
- Oh. yes. As we agreed.

390
00:29:28.686 --> 00:29:31.766
Forgive me.
but something is not quite right.

391
00:29:31.846 --> 00:29:34.766
Hmm. I thought
I brought the right amount.

392
00:29:34.846 --> 00:29:37.966
You're a busy man.
Anyone can make a mistake.

393
00:29:41.806 --> 00:29:45.166
He's yours.
Pharaoh himself would be jealous.

394
00:29:45.286 --> 00:29:47.446
Yes. he's a fine horse.

395
00:29:47.526 --> 00:29:48.886
Hmm.

396
00:29:51.046 --> 00:29:53.446
Master. I think you should see this.

397
00:29:53.526 --> 00:29:56.926
Uh... Get away from that.
Don't touch it!

398
00:29:57.006 --> 00:29:58.966
Well. look at that.

399
00:29:59.046 --> 00:30:01.406
Well. i-it's broken.

400
00:30:01.486 --> 00:30:04.766
- Your Excellency. I had no idea.
- Of course not.

401
00:30:04.846 --> 00:30:07.886
You're a busy man.
Anyone can make a mistake.

402
00:30:07.966 --> 00:30:10.406
Yours will cost you your freedom.

403
00:30:10.486 --> 00:30:13.046
Please. keep the stallion as a gift.

404
00:30:13.126 --> 00:30:15.886
No. Take him away.

405
00:30:16.926 --> 00:30:21.526
I have a dozen more horses!
Take them all! Please. anything!

406
00:30:21.606 --> 00:30:23.766
Potiphar. you should keep it.

407
00:30:23.846 --> 00:30:26.366
You said it was
the finest in all Egypt.

408
00:30:26.446 --> 00:30:31.726
Own a horse taken from a thief?
What would that say about me?

409
00:30:31.806 --> 00:30:33.246
You and your honour!

410
00:30:34.446 --> 00:30:37.606
- You've done well. What's your name?
- Joseph.

411
00:30:37.686 --> 00:30:40.966
Joseph. You're an educated slave.

412
00:30:41.046 --> 00:30:44.206
- Where did you learn?
- My father taught me.

413
00:30:44.286 --> 00:30:47.126
Ah. He taught you well.

414
00:30:47.206 --> 00:30:52.206
- What else has your father taught?
- I can read and write Egyptian.

415
00:30:52.286 --> 00:30:54.846
<i># A boy looks up</i>

416
00:30:54.926 --> 00:30:58.086
<i>- # And sees a golden gift of chance
- What a mess.</i>

417
00:30:58.166 --> 00:31:00.326
Good luck.

418
00:31:00.406 --> 00:31:02.926
<i># To prove his worth</i>

419
00:31:03.006 --> 00:31:06.806
<i># And make the best
of what might seem</i>

420
00:31:06.886 --> 00:31:09.446
<i># A dire circumstance</i>

421
00:31:09.526 --> 00:31:13.526
<i># Onward and onward
the slow and steady climb</i>

422
00:31:13.606 --> 00:31:16.006
- Master.
- Let's have a look.

423
00:31:17.566 --> 00:31:20.566
<i># Task upon task that can lift him</i>

424
00:31:20.646 --> 00:31:23.886
<i>- # To the summit over time
- Well done. Joseph.</i>

425
00:31:23.966 --> 00:31:27.806
<i># You've got to take
whatever road's at your feet</i>

426
00:31:27.886 --> 00:31:32.246
<i># You've got to make
whatever progress you can</i>

427
00:31:32.326 --> 00:31:36.286
<i># Although the map you hold
is far from complete</i>

428
00:31:36.366 --> 00:31:41.326
<i># You've got to take
whatever road's at your feet</i>

429
00:31:47.286 --> 00:31:49.926
To a good year. and to your friend.

430
00:32:20.126 --> 00:32:22.686
'My neck is killing me.

431
00:32:22.806 --> 00:32:27.086
'It's too early for this.'

432
00:32:42.446 --> 00:32:44.566
- 'Rachel.'
- Joseph.

433
00:32:44.646 --> 00:32:47.606
- Huh?
- Shh!

434
00:32:47.686 --> 00:32:49.806
W-why are you here?

435
00:32:49.886 --> 00:32:51.726
- Is something wrong?
- No.

436
00:32:51.806 --> 00:32:55.326
This land...it's not Egypt.

437
00:32:55.406 --> 00:32:56.886
Is this your home?

438
00:32:58.886 --> 00:33:03.446
- Canaan.
- Please. tell me more about Canaan.

439
00:33:05.446 --> 00:33:09.646
This is the place where I was born.

440
00:33:09.726 --> 00:33:13.966
These are the sunflowers
my mother planted.

441
00:33:14.046 --> 00:33:16.246
This is my. uh...

442
00:33:16.366 --> 00:33:18.646
- My...
- Family?

443
00:33:18.726 --> 00:33:20.766
You miss them. don't you?

444
00:33:20.886 --> 00:33:22.806
My brothers.

445
00:33:22.886 --> 00:33:24.886
They betrayed me!

446
00:33:24.966 --> 00:33:29.246
- Joseph. we are your family now.
- Huh?

447
00:33:29.326 --> 00:33:31.326
We care for you here.

448
00:33:31.406 --> 00:33:34.646
We... I feel you are special.

449
00:33:34.766 --> 00:33:38.206
What? No.
W-why have you come here tonight?

450
00:33:38.286 --> 00:33:40.886
- To be with you.
- No. This is not right.

451
00:33:40.966 --> 00:33:43.526
- Look at me.
- I won't betray my master.

452
00:33:43.606 --> 00:33:45.566
- I'm talking to you.
- No!

453
00:33:45.646 --> 00:33:49.566
- Wait! I order you to stay.
- No!

454
00:33:49.646 --> 00:33:52.126
Everything you are. you owe to me!

455
00:34:01.246 --> 00:34:03.926
You stood apart
from the other slaves.

456
00:34:04.006 --> 00:34:07.606
I let you work in my home.
I kept you from hard labour.

457
00:34:07.686 --> 00:34:09.686
and you did well for me.

458
00:34:09.766 --> 00:34:11.766
- Or so I thought.
- Master...

459
00:34:11.846 --> 00:34:16.366
No other slave was ever given this
opportunity! I gave you my trust.

460
00:34:16.446 --> 00:34:18.926
- What do you say?
- I did nothing wrong.

461
00:34:19.006 --> 00:34:21.606
Still you insult me
with your denials!

462
00:34:21.686 --> 00:34:24.566
What am I to make of this?

463
00:34:25.726 --> 00:34:29.366
It's not what it seems.
I could never betray you. master.

464
00:34:29.446 --> 00:34:33.286
Such insolence! Am I to believe
a slave over my own wife?

465
00:34:33.366 --> 00:34:35.966
I swear. I did nothing to betray you.

466
00:34:36.046 --> 00:34:42.046
Silence! For what you have done.
you must be put to death.

467
00:34:42.166 --> 00:34:45.566
- See to it.
- No. Master. I beg you. Tell him!

468
00:34:45.646 --> 00:34:49.366
Help me! Tell him that...

469
00:34:49.446 --> 00:34:52.006
Help me! Please!

470
00:34:52.086 --> 00:34:57.286
- Stop. He doesn't deserve to die.
- Why?

471
00:35:02.206 --> 00:35:04.126
I see.

472
00:35:07.126 --> 00:35:08.926
Take him to prison.

473
00:35:09.006 --> 00:35:13.806
Wait. master. No! Please!
Believe me! I- I did nothing wrong!

474
00:35:27.846 --> 00:35:29.966
This is a mistake! Uh!

475
00:35:32.366 --> 00:35:34.326
I did nothing wrong.

476
00:35:34.406 --> 00:35:37.086
Yeah. we know you're innocent.

477
00:35:59.446 --> 00:36:03.046
I know it sounds crazy.
but it was so real.

478
00:36:03.126 --> 00:36:05.566
I was up all night
with my own dreams.

479
00:36:05.646 --> 00:36:09.126
Now you wanna take up
my day with yours?

480
00:36:09.206 --> 00:36:12.166
No. Just listen.
I was back at Pharaoh's palace

481
00:36:12.246 --> 00:36:16.286
in a garden of grapes
that had three old vines.

482
00:36:16.366 --> 00:36:20.046
A tear fell from my eye.
and the vines drank it in.

483
00:36:20.126 --> 00:36:22.486
They became so thick with grapes...

484
00:36:22.566 --> 00:36:26.446
that I squeezed them into a cup
and served it to Pharaoh.

485
00:36:26.526 --> 00:36:29.126
That is quite a dream.

486
00:36:30.206 --> 00:36:34.966
- I know what your dream means.
- You do? H-how could you?

487
00:36:35.046 --> 00:36:38.286
I just do. It's some kind of gift.

488
00:36:38.366 --> 00:36:41.046
The three vines signify three days.

489
00:36:41.126 --> 00:36:45.006
Then Pharaoh will bring
you back to the palace a free man.

490
00:36:45.086 --> 00:36:48.566
- If only it were true.
- It is true.

491
00:36:48.646 --> 00:36:52.726
And when you're free. tell Pharaoh
about my gift. Please.

492
00:36:52.806 --> 00:36:57.246
Some gift. To make up fairy tales
and give hope to the foolish.

493
00:36:57.326 --> 00:37:00.886
- Maybe he's not making it up.
- All right. then.

494
00:37:00.966 --> 00:37:03.806
Here's one I've had every night
for a week.

495
00:37:03.886 --> 00:37:09.606
I'm taking three baskets of bread
to Pharaoh when the baskets fall.

496
00:37:09.686 --> 00:37:11.526
I go to pick up the bread.

497
00:37:11.606 --> 00:37:14.766
when suddenly
a swarm of birds attack me.

498
00:37:14.846 --> 00:37:18.126
They keep pecking at me
in the face and the eyes.

499
00:37:18.206 --> 00:37:20.606
What does it mean?

500
00:37:20.726 --> 00:37:23.166
- I don't know.
- Yes. you do. Tell me.

501
00:37:24.926 --> 00:37:26.886
Tell me!

502
00:37:27.806 --> 00:37:31.326
The three baskets
also signify three days.

503
00:37:31.406 --> 00:37:34.446
In three days.
Pharaoh will behead you.

504
00:37:34.526 --> 00:37:37.206
and birds will feed on your flesh.

505
00:37:37.286 --> 00:37:40.526
What? You're lying. You're lying!

506
00:37:40.606 --> 00:37:43.326
- Stop it!
- Uhh! No!

507
00:37:44.326 --> 00:37:48.206
Don't pay any attention to him.
We're not going anywhere.

508
00:38:10.126 --> 00:38:11.966
Take him.

509
00:38:12.046 --> 00:38:14.006
Get up.

510
00:38:15.886 --> 00:38:20.046
You knew. You knew!
That's not a gift!

511
00:38:20.126 --> 00:38:23.726
- That's a curse!
- Pharaoh has summoned you.

512
00:38:23.806 --> 00:38:28.126
- Why? What did I do?
- Let's go.

513
00:38:29.086 --> 00:38:31.406
It's gonna be all right. You'll see.

514
00:38:31.486 --> 00:38:33.646
- Tell Pharaoh about me.
- I will.

515
00:38:36.286 --> 00:38:38.126
Don't forget me!

516
00:38:40.086 --> 00:38:41.886
Don't forget me!

517
00:38:54.966 --> 00:38:58.926
Guard! Tell them I'm still here!

518
00:38:59.006 --> 00:39:00.726
Answer me!

519
00:39:02.446 --> 00:39:04.326
No one cares.

520
00:39:27.086 --> 00:39:28.286
Asenath!

521
00:39:28.366 --> 00:39:31.566
Halt! Who's there?

522
00:39:32.366 --> 00:39:33.966
No!

523
00:39:47.246 --> 00:39:51.126
God. why are you doing this to me?

524
00:39:51.206 --> 00:39:54.166
Do you hear me?

525
00:39:54.246 --> 00:39:56.486
Any kindness. you take away.

526
00:39:56.566 --> 00:40:00.166
You gave me the dreams.
You brought me the gift!

527
00:40:00.246 --> 00:40:05.006
Some gift! My dreams are lies.
What have I done to deserve this?

528
00:40:43.006 --> 00:40:47.286
<i># I thought I did what's right</i>

529
00:40:47.366 --> 00:40:51.486
<i># I thought I had the answers</i>

530
00:40:51.566 --> 00:40:55.966
<i># I thought I chose the surest road</i>

531
00:40:56.046 --> 00:41:00.126
<i># But that road brought me here</i>

532
00:41:01.126 --> 00:41:04.606
<i># So I put up a fight</i>

533
00:41:05.726 --> 00:41:09.886
<i># And told you how to help me</i>

534
00:41:09.966 --> 00:41:14.206
<i># Now. just when I have given up</i>

535
00:41:14.286 --> 00:41:18.406
<i># The truth is coming clear</i>

536
00:41:19.926 --> 00:41:23.126
<i># You know</i>

537
00:41:23.206 --> 00:41:26.926
<i># Better than I</i>

538
00:41:27.006 --> 00:41:29.886
<i># You know</i>

