557
00:42:35.126 --> 00:42:38.246
<i># The need to know why</i>

558
00:42:38.326 --> 00:42:41.686
<i># For you know better</i>

559
00:42:41.766 --> 00:42:46.166
<i># Than I</i>

560
00:42:46.246 --> 00:42:51.366
<i># I saw one cloud
and thought it was the sky</i>

561
00:42:52.446 --> 00:42:55.366
<i># I saw a bird and thought</i>

562
00:42:55.446 --> 00:42:59.046
<i># That I could follow</i>

563
00:42:59.126 --> 00:43:02.366
<i># But it was you
who taught that bird</i>

564
00:43:02.446 --> 00:43:04.966
<i># To fly</i>

565
00:43:05.046 --> 00:43:08.326
<i># If I let you reach me</i>

566
00:43:08.406 --> 00:43:10.966
<i># Will you teach me</i>

567
00:43:11.046 --> 00:43:15.126
<i># For you know</i>

568
00:43:15.206 --> 00:43:19.086
<i># Better than I</i>

569
00:43:19.166 --> 00:43:24.486
<i># You know the way</i>

570
00:43:24.566 --> 00:43:28.726
<i># I've let go</i>

571
00:43:28.806 --> 00:43:31.646
<i># The need to know why</i>

572
00:43:31.726 --> 00:43:35.486
<i># I'll take what answers</i>

573
00:43:35.566 --> 00:43:39.286
<i># You supply</i>

574
00:43:41.206 --> 00:43:43.766
<i># You know better</i>

575
00:43:43.846 --> 00:43:48.646
<i># Than I #</i>

576
00:44:19.526 --> 00:44:22.046
Potiphar?

577
00:44:25.126 --> 00:44:28.446
Pharaoh's butler
said you interpret dreams.

578
00:44:28.526 --> 00:44:30.806
That is true. And?

579
00:44:30.886 --> 00:44:36.286
Pharaoh is tortured by a dream.
None of his wise men can explain it.

580
00:44:36.366 --> 00:44:39.206
I'm to bring you to the palace.

581
00:44:40.766 --> 00:44:42.566
Potiphar?

582
00:44:43.886 --> 00:44:47.086
It's good to see you again.

583
00:44:51.286 --> 00:44:54.446
How could I
have allowed this to happen?

584
00:44:54.526 --> 00:44:57.606
- My wife...
- I understand.

585
00:44:58.966 --> 00:45:01.046
Let's go.

586
00:45:22.206 --> 00:45:26.526
For the sake of Egypt.
relieve my suffering.

587
00:45:49.526 --> 00:45:53.206
- Is this the one you spoke of?
- Yes. Excellency.

588
00:45:55.806 --> 00:46:00.326
I'm told you merely need to hear
a dream and you can explain it.

589
00:46:00.406 --> 00:46:04.406
Not me. Your Excellency.
The explanation comes from God.

590
00:46:04.486 --> 00:46:09.926
None of my wise men or magicians.
none of my gods could help me.

591
00:46:10.006 --> 00:46:13.766
What makes you think
your god is any different?

592
00:46:20.006 --> 00:46:22.006
Tell me your dream. Pharaoh.

593
00:46:24.406 --> 00:46:27.166
Every night it's the same.

594
00:46:29.126 --> 00:46:32.646
I am standing by the Nile.

595
00:46:32.766 --> 00:46:35.926
Seven healthy cows
graze peacefully on the banks.

596
00:46:42.926 --> 00:46:47.966
But then seven horrible.
sickly cows come from the same river.

597
00:46:48.046 --> 00:46:51.526
the most wretched
I have ever seen in Egypt.

598
00:46:52.766 --> 00:46:56.326
Suddenly they begin to devour
the healthy cattle.

599
00:46:56.406 --> 00:46:59.326
and yet the cows remain
as sickly as before.

600
00:47:00.726 --> 00:47:02.726
And then I wake up.

601
00:47:03.926 --> 00:47:08.326
- Is there more?
- Yes. Another dream always follows.

602
00:47:08.406 --> 00:47:13.046
Seven ears of grain. full and golden.
grow from a single stalk.

603
00:47:19.646 --> 00:47:22.886
Suddenly. seven ears.
hardened and scorched.

604
00:47:22.966 --> 00:47:25.126
spring up on the same stalk...

605
00:47:27.486 --> 00:47:29.526
and swallow the seven good ears.

606
00:47:31.326 --> 00:47:35.286
All that remains
are shrivelled grains unfit to eat...

607
00:47:36.446 --> 00:47:38.446
and nothing else.

608
00:47:41.126 --> 00:47:42.846
Well?

609
00:47:42.926 --> 00:47:44.966
Pharaoh's dreams are one.

610
00:47:45.046 --> 00:47:50.566
The healthy cows and ears of grain
are seven years of abundance.

611
00:47:52.526 --> 00:47:55.886
The sickly cows
and the withered grain...

612
00:47:55.966 --> 00:47:58.606
mean seven years of famine
will follow...

613
00:47:58.686 --> 00:48:00.686
and destroy the land.

614
00:48:01.766 --> 00:48:03.566
Egypt may not survive.

615
00:48:06.246 --> 00:48:09.646
Can this be stopped?
What can be done?

616
00:48:09.726 --> 00:48:11.926
You must find a man you can trust.

617
00:48:12.006 --> 00:48:14.006
During the years of plenty.

618
00:48:14.086 --> 00:48:17.886
have him collect one-fifth
of the grain from every field

619
00:48:17.966 --> 00:48:19.726
and store it under guard.

620
00:48:19.806 --> 00:48:23.526
Then. during the famine.
give it back to the people.

621
00:48:23.606 --> 00:48:26.486
Potiphar. you trust this man?

622
00:48:28.086 --> 00:48:30.046
With my life. Excellency.

623
00:48:39.406 --> 00:48:42.726
Through this man.
I have seen the future of Egypt.

624
00:48:44.766 --> 00:48:48.366
And through his deeds.
we shall prosper.

625
00:48:52.686 --> 00:48:55.766
I am giving him power over all Egypt.

626
00:48:55.846 --> 00:48:58.446
Only Pharaoh will be greater.

627
00:48:58.526 --> 00:49:01.966
You shall call him Tzafenat Paneah.

628
00:49:02.046 --> 00:49:05.006
The God speaks and He lives.

629
00:49:06.726 --> 00:49:10.366
Tzafenat Paneah! Tzafenat Paneah!

630
00:49:23.966 --> 00:49:26.406
Hey.

631
00:49:26.486 --> 00:49:30.006
Kia. come back here. Hmm.

632
00:49:34.246 --> 00:49:36.646
Tzafenat Paneah.

633
00:49:41.206 --> 00:49:43.286
Joseph.

