669
00:53:47.406 --> 00:53:50.606
Next. How many in your family?

670
00:53:50.686 --> 00:53:52.926
- Five.
- Five.

671
00:53:53.006 --> 00:53:54.966
Thank you. my lord.

672
00:53:56.646 --> 00:53:58.526
Next. please.

673
00:53:58.606 --> 00:54:01.486
- A long life for you. Excellency.
- And for you.

674
00:54:02.326 --> 00:54:05.486
Ah. here's a responsible young man.

675
00:54:05.566 --> 00:54:07.806
- How many in your family?
- Four. my lord.

676
00:54:07.886 --> 00:54:09.726
Very good.

677
00:54:14.286 --> 00:54:16.926
- Hi there. What's your name?
- Menna.

678
00:54:17.006 --> 00:54:21.486
And this is my sister Nyla.
I'm looking after her.

679
00:54:21.566 --> 00:54:25.046
Are you here for some grain too?

680
00:54:28.446 --> 00:54:31.326
- Thank you!
- Bye!

681
00:54:35.486 --> 00:54:39.686
- Here you go.
- Who's next?

682
00:54:39.766 --> 00:54:42.246
We are. my lord.

683
00:54:43.486 --> 00:54:46.566
- You are not Egyptian.
- No. sir.

684
00:54:46.646 --> 00:54:49.806
My brothers and I
have travelled far. from Canaan.

685
00:54:56.446 --> 00:54:59.566
- Joseph. what's wrong?
- Nothing.

686
00:54:59.646 --> 00:55:02.086
Look at you. You're shaking.

687
00:55:02.166 --> 00:55:04.446
I-it must be the sun. I'll be fine.

688
00:55:04.526 --> 00:55:06.806
Our families are hungry.

689
00:55:06.926 --> 00:55:09.766
You haven't contributed
to our supply.

690
00:55:09.846 --> 00:55:13.286
We don't ask for charity.
We'll pay you with silver.

691
00:55:17.326 --> 00:55:19.326
How many are there?

692
00:55:19.406 --> 00:55:23.886
12. 10 here and at home we have
our father and youngest brother.

693
00:55:23.966 --> 00:55:26.006
Give them...

694
00:55:26.086 --> 00:55:28.086
Nothing!

695
00:55:28.166 --> 00:55:32.686
10 foreigners asking
for grain. no ties to Egypt.

696
00:55:32.766 --> 00:55:36.446
Are you thieves. hoping to see
where we store our grain?

697
00:55:36.526 --> 00:55:40.286
I don't know what you are.
but I don't believe your story.

698
00:55:40.366 --> 00:55:43.406
Your Excellency.
everything we say is true.

699
00:55:43.486 --> 00:55:46.486
Prove it!
Produce this youngest brother.

700
00:55:46.566 --> 00:55:50.046
- But what would that prove?
- That you're not lying.

701
00:55:50.126 --> 00:55:52.926
If it's the truth.
I'll let you buy grain.

702
00:55:53.006 --> 00:55:56.526
Till then. arrest this one!

703
00:55:56.606 --> 00:55:59.606
Until you produce this brother.

704
00:55:59.686 --> 00:56:01.886
Take him.

705
00:56:01.966 --> 00:56:03.886
Stop!

706
00:56:03.966 --> 00:56:07.606
- Judah. help me!
- No!

707
00:56:07.686 --> 00:56:10.566
- No! No! No!
- Let's go.

708
00:56:17.286 --> 00:56:20.246
Joseph. what are you doing?

709
00:56:20.326 --> 00:56:22.606
They're only feeding their families.

710
00:56:22.686 --> 00:56:26.406
They're thieves.
here to steal our grain.

711
00:56:26.486 --> 00:56:28.846
They needed food and they would pay.

712
00:56:28.926 --> 00:56:32.766
How can you say they're thieves?
They've done nothing to you.

713
00:56:35.086 --> 00:56:37.166
Nothing?

714
00:56:41.766 --> 00:56:44.926
- They're my brothers.
- What?

715
00:56:45.006 --> 00:56:50.326
They sold me.
They sold me into slavery.

716
00:56:50.406 --> 00:56:52.846
They took me away from my home.

717
00:56:52.926 --> 00:56:55.646
I never got
to say goodbye to my mother.

718
00:56:55.726 --> 00:56:59.086
I never got
to see my father grow old.

719
00:57:01.526 --> 00:57:05.486
Joseph. I... I didn't know.

720
00:57:05.566 --> 00:57:10.126
You're here now. You have a home.
a wife who loves you.

721
00:57:10.206 --> 00:57:12.766
everything you could want.

722
00:57:12.846 --> 00:57:15.366
No. Not everything.

723
00:57:19.246 --> 00:57:22.446
I thought you learned something
in that cell.

724
00:57:23.326 --> 00:57:26.126
Remember when
I would bring food to you?

725
00:57:26.206 --> 00:57:29.966
Yes. It kept me going.

726
00:57:37.406 --> 00:57:40.366
Hey! You won't keep me here.

727
00:57:40.446 --> 00:57:42.606
My brothers will come for me.

728
00:57:42.686 --> 00:57:45.126
My brothers will come...

729
00:57:47.446 --> 00:57:48.846
Joseph.

730
00:57:52.926 --> 00:57:57.126
<i># How long must there be anger here</i>

731
00:57:57.206 --> 00:58:00.526
<i># Before we can rejoice</i>

732
00:58:00.606 --> 00:58:04.526
<i># Embracing love instead of fear</i>

733
00:58:04.606 --> 00:58:08.286
<i># Is but a simple choice</i>

734
00:58:09.566 --> 00:58:12.926
<i># It's hard for me to see you fall</i>

735
00:58:13.006 --> 00:58:16.646
<i># So bitter and so blind</i>

736
00:58:16.726 --> 00:58:21.446
<i># When the truest nature of us all</i>

737
00:58:21.526 --> 00:58:25.446
<i># Invites us to be kind</i>

738
00:58:25.526 --> 00:58:29.526
<i># Bloom. bloom. may you know</i>

739
00:58:29.606 --> 00:58:33.446
<i># The wisdom only time breeds</i>

740
00:58:33.526 --> 00:58:37.446
<i># There's room. bloom and you'll grow</i>

741
00:58:37.526 --> 00:58:42.246
<i># To follow where your heart leads</i>

742
00:58:42.326 --> 00:58:45.886
<i># Bloom and may you live</i>

743
00:58:45.966 --> 00:58:50.166
<i># The way your life was meant to be</i>

744
00:58:50.246 --> 00:58:52.766
<i># There's room.
bloom and forgive... #</i>

745
00:58:52.846 --> 00:58:54.446
Tzafenat Paneah...

746
00:58:54.526 --> 00:58:57.686
The family of Canaanites...
They've returned.

747
00:58:57.766 --> 00:58:59.406
Thank you.

748
00:59:00.086 --> 00:59:03.606
Maybe they've suffered
these last 20 years as well.

749
00:59:03.686 --> 00:59:05.726
- Maybe they've changed.
- No.

750
00:59:05.806 --> 00:59:07.806
I don't think so.

751
00:59:14.406 --> 00:59:16.646
Don't speak unless you're spoken to.

752
00:59:19.806 --> 00:59:22.566
Don't worry. It'll be all right.

753
00:59:34.046 --> 00:59:36.046
Welcome.

754
00:59:36.126 --> 00:59:40.846
- You've done what I've asked?
- Our brother. Benjamin.

755
00:59:51.566 --> 00:59:55.566
You kept your word.
Bring out the other brother.

756
00:59:55.646 --> 01:00:01.006
So. Benjamin.
tell me of your mother and father.

757
01:00:01.086 --> 01:00:04.646
My mother is no longer alive.

758
01:00:04.726 --> 01:00:08.566
Oh. I- I'm sorry.

759
01:00:09.846 --> 01:00:11.886
And your father?

760
01:00:11.966 --> 01:00:15.046
- He's worried I'm here.
- Why is that?

761
01:00:15.126 --> 01:00:20.446
- I'm a long way from home.
- Oh? Doesn't he trust your brothers?

762
01:00:20.526 --> 01:00:23.006
He likes me to stay close by.

763
01:00:23.086 --> 01:00:25.846
Really? Why is that?

764
01:00:27.406 --> 01:00:30.526
A long time ago.
h-he lost his youngest son.

765
01:00:30.606 --> 01:00:33.886
Well. I'm sorry to hear that.
How did that happen?

766
01:00:33.966 --> 01:00:36.526
- He was killed.
- Killed? How?

767
01:00:36.606 --> 01:00:38.406
By wolves.

768
01:00:38.486 --> 01:00:42.366
- Wolves?
- Yes.

769
01:00:42.446 --> 01:00:45.086
It broke my father's heart.

770
01:00:45.166 --> 01:00:50.326
Well. it must have been very hard
on your brothers too.

771
01:00:50.406 --> 01:00:53.566
- They never speak of it.
- Don't they?

772
01:00:53.686 --> 01:00:56.686
- Benjamin!
- Simeon!

773
01:00:56.766 --> 01:01:00.006
I was beginning to worry.

774
01:01:00.086 --> 01:01:04.446
You must be hungry
after your journey. Come.

775
01:01:04.526 --> 01:01:07.366
You'll be my guests.

776
01:01:32.766 --> 01:01:34.726
A toast...

777
01:01:35.926 --> 01:01:37.486
to brothers.

778
01:01:37.566 --> 01:01:40.286
To brothers!

779
01:02:03.246 --> 01:02:06.686
Stop this. You have no right.
We've done nothing wrong.

780
01:02:10.006 --> 01:02:14.166
What's going on?
Why have they been arrested?

781
01:02:14.246 --> 01:02:17.166
- Joseph. what are you doing?
- You'll see.

782
01:02:18.046 --> 01:02:20.966
Get back in place. Get back in...

783
01:02:21.086 --> 01:02:25.206
I give you food.
I take you into my home.

784
01:02:25.286 --> 01:02:29.086
And this is how you repay me.
by stealing?

785
01:02:29.166 --> 01:02:31.046
We wouldn't steal from you!

786
01:02:31.126 --> 01:02:33.766
- And now you insult me by lying.
- What?

787
01:02:33.846 --> 01:02:36.846
One of you has stolen from me.

788
01:02:45.446 --> 01:02:47.526
Benjamin.

789
01:02:54.206 --> 01:02:57.166
- No...
- The favoured one.

790
01:02:57.246 --> 01:02:59.006
- I didn't!
- Arrest him.

791
01:02:59.086 --> 01:03:01.886
For this you will be punished.

792
01:03:01.966 --> 01:03:05.206
- Someone put it there!
- Stop! Take me instead.

793
01:03:05.326 --> 01:03:08.206
- No. take me.
- Take me!

794
01:03:08.286 --> 01:03:11.206
- Take me!
- Take any of us. your grace.

795
01:03:11.286 --> 01:03:13.646
but. please. let the boy go.

796
01:03:13.726 --> 01:03:18.326
You would sacrifice yourselves
for a spoiled half-brother?

797
01:03:18.406 --> 01:03:19.766
Yes.

798
01:03:20.966 --> 01:03:25.486
Why should you care if I take him.
beat him. make him a slave?

799
01:03:25.566 --> 01:03:30.606
Because I will not
make my father suffer...again.

800
01:03:33.526 --> 01:03:36.886
Again? What do you mean. "again"?

801
01:03:39.526 --> 01:03:42.326
Our brother was not killed by wolves.

802
01:03:43.606 --> 01:03:47.486
We were blinded by jealousy
and sold him into slavery.

803
01:03:47.566 --> 01:03:50.606
For 20 years
we have lived with that guilt.

804
01:03:51.966 --> 01:03:54.406
We can't go back without the boy.

805
01:03:54.486 --> 01:03:57.246
My father could not bear it
a second time.

806
01:03:57.326 --> 01:03:59.886
And neither could we.

807
01:03:59.966 --> 01:04:03.646
If anyone is to be punished.
it should be us.

808
01:04:20.446 --> 01:04:23.966
I will not harm any of you
or our father.

809
01:04:26.686 --> 01:04:28.446
I am your brother. Joseph.

810
01:04:28.526 --> 01:04:33.006
- Joseph?
- I can't believe you're here.

811
01:04:33.086 --> 01:04:35.526
How can it be?

812
01:04:35.606 --> 01:04:36.966
Joseph?

813
01:04:38.046 --> 01:04:42.566
I have so much to tell you.
so many questions to ask.

814
01:04:42.646 --> 01:04:46.526
Oh. Joseph. can you ever forgive us?

815
01:04:48.206 --> 01:04:50.846
I already have.

816
01:04:50.926 --> 01:04:55.486
Can you forgive me for thinking
I was some miracle from God?

817
01:04:55.566 --> 01:04:57.606
But you are a miracle.

818
01:04:57.686 --> 01:05:01.006
God sent you to save our family
and all of Egypt.

819
01:05:01.086 --> 01:05:04.126
- And you did.
- Asenath?

820
01:05:04.206 --> 01:05:07.726
Please. I'd like you
to meet my brothers.

821
01:05:09.086 --> 01:05:12.446
Welcome. Pleasure to meet you.

822
01:05:12.526 --> 01:05:14.366
You will join me here.

823
01:05:14.446 --> 01:05:17.406
all of you. with your families.

824
01:05:24.566 --> 01:05:26.566
Look!

825
01:05:33.726 --> 01:05:36.926
- I see him! There he is!
- It's him! There he is!

826
01:05:38.686 --> 01:05:41.726
- Joseph!
- Father.

827
01:05:43.806 --> 01:05:46.846
Father! Father!

828
01:05:52.006 --> 01:05:54.486
- Father!
- Joseph.

829
01:05:54.566 --> 01:05:58.046
My boy. My boy.

830
01:05:58.126 --> 01:06:01.526
Your mother prayed
this day would come.

831
01:06:01.606 --> 01:06:04.686
that we'd all be together again
as a family.

832
01:06:04.766 --> 01:06:09.926
- It's a miracle.
- Yes. Father. It is a miracle.

